# Shell scripts and git hooks must stay LF-only: with core.autocrlf=true a
# checkout would otherwise rewrite them to CRLF, and Git for Windows runs hooks
# through sh, which rejects a CRLF `#!/bin/sh` line with a "bad interpreter"
# error. Pinning the line endings keeps them runnable on every platform.
*.sh text eol=lf
.githooks/** text eol=lf
